This paper is primarily focused on cryptography and security, making cs.CR the most likely sub-category. It also involves decentralized networks and infrastructure, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the sharing of sensitive data, which could relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
